function count_model_rows(df_cars)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> first --> size -> length(size[1])
end
```

This function groups the data by the `model` column and then returns the number of rows for each model. It uses the `groupby` function to group the data, followed by a chain operator (`|>`) to pipe the result into another function that takes the first element of the grouped data (using `first`) and extracts the size of the first group (using `size`), and finally returns the length of that group as the result.
